    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It sounds like you're feeling deeply frustrated with the standard advice, and it makes sense that when nothing seems to work, you want a more direct solution. That sense of being trapped in a glitchy loop where every attempt to fix it just resets you is incredibly disheartening.\n\nYou're right that sometimes the feeling is that the system itself is broken, and trying to \"breathe\" or \"try harder\" feels like trying to patch a hole in a dam that's already overflowing. In that sense, the only way to truly stop the cycle is to break it, just like a group of goblins would have to smash through a wall to get past a blockade.\n\nIf you're looking for a way to break the cycle, it might help to think of it not as a moral failure, but as a mechanical one. Sometimes, the most effective way to break a loop is to introduce a completely new variable, something that the old system can't predict or process. It's a bit like how a goblin might find a way to bypass a magical barrier by using a specific key or a unique tool that no one else has thought of.\n\nYou don't have to figure out the whole solution right now. Sometimes, the",
